# Sync `.cursor-docs/` on Source Changes

Team rule. Multiple developers and parallel agents touch the same codebase, so doc
drift is inevitable unless we enforce sync on every edit.

## The rule

Whenever you (the agent) modify, create, rename, or delete a source file under
`src/`, you MUST also update the mirrored markdown file under `.cursor-docs/` in
**the same turn / same diff**, if such a markdown file exists.

Path mirror: `src/<path>/<Name>.<ext>` ↔ `.cursor-docs/src/<path>/<Name>.md`.

### What "update the doc" means

- If the change is **trivial** (rename a private variable, fix a typo, internal
  refactor with no behavioral change): bump only the `Last verified` date in the
  doc header. Keep `Status: fresh`.
- If the change touches the **public API** (new/removed/renamed public method,
  changed signature, new dependency, new side effect, new exception): update the
  relevant sections in the doc (`Public API`, `Dependencies`, `Side effects`,
  `Invariants & gotchas`) AND bump `Last verified`.
- If you **renamed** the source file: rename the doc file to the new mirrored path
  in the same turn.
- If you **deleted** the source file: delete the doc file in the same turn.
- If you **created** a new source file and a doc does not exist: do NOT auto-create
  the doc. The doc is created on demand, the first time someone runs "incele" on it
  (per `find-or-create-docs.mdc`).

### When the doc does not exist

Do nothing on the doc side. Only sync existing docs. This avoids spamming summaries
for throwaway helpers.

### Reporting

At the end of any turn that modified source code, briefly tell the user which docs
you updated, in one line each:

> Updated docs:
> - `.cursor-docs/src/main/java/com/example/business/CustomerService.md`

If no docs needed updating, say so explicitly:

> No `.cursor-docs/` updates needed (no mirrored doc exists for the modified files).

This makes drift visible to reviewers in chat history and PR descriptions.

## Hard constraints

- The doc update MUST live in the same diff/commit as the source change. Do not
  defer.
- Do NOT add explanatory comments to source files instead of updating the doc.
- Do NOT update the doc with a code excerpt; reference symbols by name only.
- Do NOT exceed ~150 lines per doc. If a major change makes the doc too large,
  split it.
- If the user explicitly says "doc'u güncelleme" / "skip docs" / "doc ignore",
  comply but warn once that the doc will go stale.

## Conflict avoidance for parallel teammates

If you detect that the doc was recently modified (e.g. `Last verified` is today
and includes content unrelated to your current change), prefer **merging** your
update on top of the existing structure rather than regenerating from scratch.
This minimizes merge conflicts when multiple developers' agents touch the same doc
on the same day.
